# Third-Party Licenses

Octa is distributed under the [MIT License](LICENSE). It bundles a number
of open-source Rust crates whose licenses require attribution. The table
below lists every transitive dependency and its SPDX license expression.

The full text of each unique license is shipped in the `licenses/`
directory alongside this file (one file per SPDX identifier). License
families used in this build include MIT, Apache-2.0, BSD-2-Clause,
BSD-3-Clause, BSL-1.0, CC0-1.0, CDLA-Permissive-2.0, ISC, OFL-1.1,
Ubuntu-font-1.0, Unicode-3.0, and Zlib.

This file is generated automatically from `Cargo.lock` by `cargo about`.
Do not edit by hand.

